inlineContent.text: The intent object containing details about the user’s request. Use this object to get the initial information, if any, provided by the user.
The block to execute with the resolution. You must execute this block at some point during your implementation of this method. This block has no return value and takes the following parameter:
The object containing the details of your proposed resolution. For successful resolutions, create a resolution object with the name of the user’s car.
Implement this method to resolve the name of the user’s car. If the app has access to more than one car, use the intent’s
property to identify the correct car. If the app has access to only a single car, you can call the completion block with a
resolution for Objective-C, to indicate that the app doesn’t need the car name.

abstract.text: Empower people to customize interactions for your app on their device.
A request to change the seat-related settings in a CarPlay-enabled vehicle.
The name of the car you applied the settings to.
The handler interface for changing a vehicle’s seat-related settings.
Resolves whether you can enable the seat cooling system.
Resolves whether you can enable the seat heating system.
Resolves whether you can enable the seat massage system.
Resolves the intensity level of the requested system.
Resolves the requested relative qualifier for the intensity level.
A resolution result for a speakable string object associated with an intent.
The return type of functions that don’t explicitly specify a return type, that is, an empty tuple `()`.
